Peter Dada, Akure The All Progressives Congress ward Chairman in Ondo State, Mr James Ajulo, who was kidnapped by gunmen last Sunday has been released . Ajulo, who is the party chairman in Ward 13, Akungba Akoko in the Akoko South-West Local Government Area of the state was kidnapped in front of his residence in the Ibaka area of Akungba. Few days after the abduction, the kidnappers demanded N10m. It was gathered on Thursday that he was released on Wednesday in Ado Ekiti, Ekiti State. One of the friends of the victim, Mr Tolu Babaleye , who confirmed the development, said the hoodlums set the victim free after collecting N2.5m. Babaleye said, “Ajulo James has been released by his abductors in Ado Ekiti after the payment of N2.5m. We are grateful to everyone that showed concern.”’ Similarly,  the abducted 70- year-old woman, Mrs Fehintola Wewe, has also regained her freedom. Wewe, who was abducted on 13 Broad Street, Sabomi, in the Ese Odo Local Government Area of the state by gunmen, was said to have been released in Lekki, Lagos. It was not confirmed if ransom was paid before she was released. The state Police Public Relations Officer, CSP Femi Joseph, confirmed the release of the two victims, saying investigation was ongoing into the matter. “As we are investigating the matter; we are searching for the hoodlums and they will soon be arrested. On the ransom, I am not aware of that, “the PPRO said. Copyright PUNCH.
